#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

cat <<USAGE
Moodle Claude Runner

This command surface manages the Moodle checkout and moodle-docker workflow.
Run all ./bin/* commands from the claude harness repo root, not the parent Moodle checkout.
Chrome, Firefox, and Atlassian MCP servers are configured in the Claude Code client.
Agentic orchestrator is expected separately for non-trivial Moodle discovery tasks.
Verify it in the sibling repo at ~/projects/agentic_orchestrator, not in ~/projects/moodle/claude.
In practice, verify it there with the verify command plus a real query or pilot-run.

Core lifecycle:
  ./bin/up [compose-args...]           Start services
  ./bin/down [compose-args...]         Stop services
  ./bin/ps [compose-args...]           Show service status
  ./bin/logs [service...]              Follow docker logs
  ./bin/doctor                         Validate env and docker wiring
  ./bin/upgrade [upgrade-args...]      Run Moodle CLI upgrade in the web container
  ./bin/smoke                          Run a lightweight harness smoke test
  ./bin/feature-smoke [flags...]       Run a real install + PHPUnit + Behat smoke workflow

Moodle setup and tests:
  ./bin/install [install-args...]
  ./bin/phpunit-init [args...]
  ./bin/phpunit [test/filter...]
  ./bin/behat-init [args...]
  ./bin/behat [args...]
  ./bin/grunt [grunt-args...]         Run Moodle Grunt from the parent checkout

Quality checks:
  ./bin/phpcs <path...>                Run host PHPCS using the moodle standard
  ./bin/phpcbf <path...>               Run host PHPCBF using the moodle standard
  ./bin/changed-files [base-ref]       List changed files against an explicit or auto-detected base
  ./bin/preflight [paths...]           Run the normal targeted PHPCS pass
  ./bin/preflight --changed-lines      Focus PHPCS on changed lines in tracked files and full new files
  ./bin/jira-update <issue> [options]  Update common Jira fields/comments through REST fallback
  ./bin/phpcs-changed [--base-ref ref] [path...]
                                       Advanced helper behind preflight --changed-lines

Admin login defaults:
  MOODLE_ADMIN_USERNAME=admin, MOODLE_ADMIN_PASSWORD=test
  Use these for browser validation unless overridden in .claude.env

PHPCS defaults:
  PHPCS_BIN=phpcs, PHPCBF_BIN=phpcbf, PHPCS_STANDARD=moodle
  Set PHPCS_STANDARD=moodle-extra for a stricter pass when needed
  Use ./bin/preflight --changed-lines for legacy-file edits where only the new
  or changed lines should be held to current PHPCS expectations

JavaScript / Grunt guidance:
  Edit Moodle AMD source files in amd/src/ and treat amd/build/*.min.js as
  generated output. Do not hand-edit built files unless a task is explicitly
  about generated/vendor assets and that choice is justified.
  Prefer targeted Grunt runs, for example:
    ./bin/grunt amd --files=public/mod/example/amd/src/widget.js
    ./bin/grunt amd --root=public/mod/example
  Use broader tasks like ./bin/grunt js only when the change genuinely spans
  AMD, YUI, and React/ESM build surfaces.

Author metadata:
  Copy .claude.identity.example to .claude.identity and set AUTHOR_NAME,
  AUTHOR_EMAIL, and COPYRIGHT_YEAR for generated Moodle file headers
  If .claude.identity is missing, stop before generating new Moodle source files
  unless the user explicitly approves a fallback

Scheduled task validation:
  Expected acceptance path: ./bin/preflight, ./bin/upgrade, targeted PHPUnit,
  explicit admin/cli/scheduled_task.php --execute='\component\task\classname' --force, admin login at
  /admin/tool/task/scheduledtasks.php, and confirmation of a safe observable effect

Container command helpers:
  ./bin/web <command...>               Exec in web service as WEBSERVER_USER
  ./bin/web-root <command...>          Exec in web service as default/root user
  ./bin/mdc <compose-args...>          Raw moodle-docker-compose passthrough

Behat path guidance:
  ./bin/behat accepts option-style args like --tags=@tagname
  and targeted feature paths such as:
    ./bin/behat public/local/example/tests/behat/example.feature
    ./bin/behat local/example/tests/behat/example.feature
  The wrapper normalizes supported feature paths to container-visible
  absolute paths before invoking Moodle's Behat runner.
USAGE
